@NODE "Introduction" "Introduction"
@TOC "Main"

@{FG SHINE}____________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
                           I N T R O D U C T I O N
@{FG SHINE}____________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
   T2S is a little WB program, which loads up a little window at the bottom 
of your Workbench screen, and while picking lottery numbers displays some 
(sometimes) funny messages on the windows title bar. It also plays music in 
the background, which will really get on your nerves!

   @{" Back to the Contents Page! " LINK "Main"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Requirements" "Requirements"
@TOC "Main"

@{FG SHINE}____________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
                           R E Q U I R E M E N T S
@{FG SHINE}____________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
   I can only guarantee that T2S works on my A1200, with WB 3.0, but i`m 
sure it will work on any Amiga and WB version, if you have an A1200 and WB 
3.0 and it still does not work see @{" Errors/Bugs " LINK "KnownBugs"} for more information!  

 @{" Back to the Contents Page! " LINK "Main"}
@ENDNODE

